Colombia Stocks: Ecopetrol, Grupo Sura, Fabricato, Enka Rise

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-05-10T16:05:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-10/colombia-stocks-ecopetrol-grupo-sura-fabricato-enka-rise.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:39 a.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index rose 1 percent to 14,135.91 while the Colcap
Index also gained 1 percent to 1,686.50, as liquidity returns to
the market after Avianca Taca Holding SA and Grupo Aval Acciones
y Valores (AVAL CB) ended oversubscribed share issuances that
will begin trading this week, said Camilo Rubiano, analyst at
Afin Sa.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  , Colombia’s largest oil company,
rose 2.8 percent to 3,880 pesos. Chilean and Peruvian pension
funds are also buying up the state-run company’s stock ahead of
Colombia’s May 30 bourse integration with the two countries,
Rubiano said.  Grupo de Inversiones Suramericana SA (GRUPOSUR)  , the
parent company of Colombia’s largest bank, climbed as much as
1.7 percent to 36,980 pesos after a person familiar with the
transaction said the company plans to sell $300 million of 10-
year bonds as soon as May 12.  Textile companies rose on speculation the  U.S. Congress  may
approve a free-trade agreement with Colombia within months,
Rubiano said.  Enka de Colombia SA (ENKA)  , a Medellin-based synthetic
fibers producer, rose 0.8 percent to 13.1 pesos.  Textiles Fabricato Tejicondor SA (FABRI)  , Colombia’s
biggest textile maker, gained as much as 2.9 percent to 49.5
pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
